Author: rngcoin
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Warning Latoken exchange is possibly SCAM for now.  We've submited the listing application in 8th of February. We had a conversationg with Latoken representative by email (all details will provided later). We've verified details and Latoken support confirms that this person is representative of latoken. We've paid 1.5 btc for the listing. We've wait about one month, when our patience is over we describe the situation in latoken official telegram group https://t.me/latoken Official representative @LATOKEN_CS has contacted us directly by private chat. He said everything is fine and they will list it asap. After that he asked a very strange thing: LATOKEN, [03.03.19 16:18] You're required to activate your coin on our database as the final procedure to be done then your coin will be listed  Rng Coin, [03.03.19 16:19] How should we do that?  LATOKEN, [03.03.19 16:19] A link will be generated and used in synchronizing your coin  LATOKEN, [03.03.19 16:20] The system requires the TX hash of a refundable minimal deposit fee in generating the link Note:-your deposit will be sent back to you immediately after your coin has been activated  You're required to make a minimal deposit fee of 500$ worth of btc to our activation address Note:-your deposit will be sent back to you immediately after your coin has been activated  It was very strange, but as it was described that "your deposit will be sent back to you immediately" we've sent the funds.  Next day the support said:  LATOKEN, [04.03.19 20:31] You tokens was activated with the deposit you sent  LATOKEN, [04.03.19 20:32] Now the system requires an activation code generated for you to complete the listing process and to process the refunding processing  LATOKEN, [04.03.19 20:41] But we need you to make a deposit again But all your deposit will be sent back to you immediately  LATOKEN, [04.03.19 20:42] We will announce your coin  immediately your listing process is completed  LATOKEN, [04.03.19 20:46] The activation code deposit is 200$ worth of btc And all your total funds of 700$ worth of btc will be sent back to you fully immediately your listing process is completed  When I said that it's all sounds like a scam and I'll post this info in bitcointalk, received the following response:  LATOKEN, [04.03.19 20:54] You post it then your coin will not be listed Will posting this solve your issue You post it then you lose all your listing fee and all your activation deposit You only need to have your activation code generated and everything will be fine  It seem like the Latoken exchange is scam for now.

Body: Bitcoin Garden: Ex director of World Quant joins LATOKEN https://bitcoingarden.org/ex-director-of-world-quant-joins-latoken/  Starting from March, 15th Leonid Merkin, who used to be a general director of World Quant and vice-president of Goldman Sachs, will take the position of CIO (Chief Information Officer) at LATOKEN digital assets exchange. LATOKEN’s representative noted that as CIO Leonid Merkin will lead software development department. He will concentrate on the implementation of derivatives market and infrastructure for institutional traders.       “Leonid is well-known as one of the leading specialists in HFT (High-Frequency Trading) algorithms in London and Moscow. His experience and professional background will speed up the migration of capital markets to the blockchain exchange,” — stated the founder and CEO of LATOKEN Valentin Preobrazhenskiy.   Previously Leonid Merkin used to be the head of World Quant’s office in Russia having 5  billions dollars in terms of fiduciary management. He also was Managing Director in Alfa-Bank, where he was leading HFT and Quantitative Analytics department;  Global Head of Interest Rates Algorithmic Trading Quantitative Analytics in RBS (Royal Bank of Scotland); Executive director in UBS, Credit Agricole CIB....

Author: kerhso
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Good day! Our weekly Dev Update is ready. A lot of internal updates were done, and a lot of new functions are coming.  1. C++ high-performant matching engine. We started process of integration matching engine capable to process 2 000 000 of transactions per seconds. It will replace our current solution and give us ability to scale up to 5-6 millions of active users on our platform.  2. Kubernates-based microservices architecture. We are in the process of migration from our current architecture to the new one, which will give amazing speed for LA Platform. Each part of the system such as auth engine, assets listing, market data, etc. will become from 20 to 170 times faster.  3. Lightning-based network for processing trades. We are in the process of researching Lighting Network as a possible solution for decentralized exchange. First controlled transactions are done, so the next steps is to integrate Lightning Payment channels to the current matching engine. It will give us ability to process traded in peer-to-peer mode, without any deposits or withdrawals to the centralized exchange.  Stay tuned!

Author: rehydrogenated
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Ah another middleman token. I do think these will make it easier to own weird assets worldwide. LAtoken might even be the one that takes off and gets adopted by the mainstream and hedge funds in order to diversify. Now people can diversify into assets they could not touch previously. I think art is a great example. How do you invest in a $50 million painting if you can't afford it. The only way currently is to invest in a hedge fund that will buy that painting and try to resell it eventually. Only qualified investors can invest in such funds and the fees are usually very steep. If LAtoken can fix these problems it will be much easier to diversify outside of the normal stock and bond markets. I can't wait for the opportunity to invest in something that is not correlated to either the stock or bonds markets. That way I have some safety if their is a market collapse.  Good luck dev team!

Author: cryptopete
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Guys this is very bad the way that they handled this ICO.  If we didn't get scammed they are particularly greedy.  Up until yesterday they kept saying our tokens could be withdrawn on October 11th, Now they are saying at the end of the month.  They are still offering their tokens more than 12 hours after the ICO ended.  You can literally go on their website, sign up and purchase on the ICO.  They are selling tokens from their company pool of LAT while we are stuck with ours until we fill out additional KYC information. How can they be allowed to sell their own tokens (at a fixed price of .001512) from company pool while i'm stuck here holding mine and I can't do anything with them?   The KYC information is supposed to take 7 days to review.  However, as a US resident, I can't even trade on the platform.  Myself and others were banned from their telegram chat for asking about these shady practices.  Good luck everyone.  Feel like my money got stolen here, but I will hold out hope for the best.

Body: The LA Token whitepaper mentions that US residents can participate because the LAT token is not considered as a security with the exception that the US residents cannot use some of the other features like the asset backed tokens on their platform. So US residents participated. Now there's an issue where this is not the case and that the LAT token may be considered as a security which can cause problems with the SEC regulations. That's why for most ICOs US residents cannot participate in ICOs. I think they also stopped allowing US residents to participate for the time being.  Someone feel free to correct me if my understanding wasn't correct.  Update: They're preparing a post for the US market with the plan on how to go about this.

Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Imho, this is how it works with LATOKEN:  1- One Lithuanian guys puts, let's say 10% of his house on the platform. At a price P1. These 10% are conditioned to the sale of the house, and the deal has to end at a given time.  2- One Ethiopian guys buys this 10% "SHARE" of the house that will be vested until the house is sold.  then we have 2 options:  a- the house is sold: the Ethiopian guy gets the money (10% of the price sold, as a liquidized asset, ideally with a P2 price premium vs the original P1 price (P2>P1) b- the house is NOT sold: the Lithuanian guy has to buy buy back the Tokens from the Ethiopian guy. It's done via smart contracts, the money being "sort of" locked  during the vesting period (time between tokenization/liquidization and end-of-sale defined period)

Author: stupid_seb
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: FOMO: Fear of Missing Out example: people buying high fearing that they will miss out a super deal. They generally buy too high, and shill the coin hoping it will raise.  BOMO: my own invention: Bitterness of having missed out example: people did not buy a coin and are now jealous of other holders They spread fud in order to get the price low, either to buy, or just for their own little satisfaction. Bomos are the worst kind...

Author: dusty_daniel
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: The process is as follows: 1) LAToken issues tokens linked to the price of publicly traded assets (e.g. an Apple share) 2) Cryptoholders buy asset tokens at an auction on the LAT platform using cryptocurrency 3) On a pre-determined settlement date, LAToken buys back asset tokens from cryptoholders at the current market price of the underlying asset (e.g. current market price of an Apple share on the NASDAQ)

Author: Greenlee
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Either at the day expiration or before that a client may choose to trade out of his position by simply selling it or by waiting till the end of the expiration day and receive respective amount of LAT in return for expired contract. The expiration price will be calculated as a close price of real world asset (Apple share on respective exchange for example) for that trading day divided by the average rate of LAT/EUR over 24 hours (if we will be able to list LAT on exchange before the end of September), or by an average rate of ETH/EUR over 24 hours times the fixed price of LAT/ETH depending on ICO round). The company runs market making operations currently, thus the bids are available 24/7. A client is free to choose either to hold his tokenized shares till last day of trading or trade off his position before that.   Currently a small number of early adopters test the waters and in parallel we build market-making facilities in house. But as the process and transparency develop we expect more people to express their opinions with regards to forwards on what stocks they want to trade on our platform and consequently tokenize those real world assets for trading.

Author: panteraforlife
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: As for us as LAToken investors.  Valentin Preobrazhenskiy, CEO at LAToken, explains that his company has responded to the development by putting all of its activities related to China on hold: “We were about to participate in Blockchain conferences and meetups there, but cancelled our roadshow in mainland China. We also don’t accept contributions from Chinese citizens and residents at the moment. However, the Chinese ban doesn’t affect our activities in other countries, and we still proceed with our token sale as scheduled.” Preobrazhenskiy acknowledges the negative sentiment created by the development in China as is evident in the market behaviour. Bitcoin price quickly bounced, while Ethereum, the most popular currency for ICOs, is still in a holding pattern as markets worry that other operations with cryptocurrencies may be banned by Chinese regulators as well. Another anxiety trigger comes with the fears, that other regulators might follow Chinese ruling and ban token sales instead of regulating. Preobrazhenskiy notes that along with cancelling all the activities related to China, his company has introduced a representation form, that stops Chinese investors from investing in the aftermath of the ban.(C)  But this is more in the short term for me.

Author: mtnminer
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: In the short term, China’s ban on ICOs and shutting down of exchanges is bearish for ETH and BTC because: - A lot of the hot money from China leaves the ICO, Bitcoin and Ethereum markets. - Some hot money cryptocurrency buyers will, at the margin, buy less or not buy. Some will not bother using VPNs, exchanging Chinese Yuan for US dollars or gold on the black market, or taking trips to island jurisdictions like Malta or to Switzerland to open up accounts to move assets including cryptcurrencies around.   Chinese regulators and other government officials need time to figure out how to regulate cryptocurrencies, including ICO tokens.

Author: panteraforlife
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: For the long term - China is trying to become the most powerful economy, so it uses all the latest and most effective "money technologies". ICO is one of the most promising now. I think that the ICO ban will be temporary.

The flaws of the traditional system can not be eliminated so easily. A significant part of them also clings to the cryptocurrencies system.

Body: For all contributors who have worries about SEC:  Gil Penchina from IDG Ventures says in a TechCrunch article, that SEC shows support for ICOs that are not securities, and explains, why LAToken is compliant with all the regulation:  “LAToken platform .. is not launching in the US operations which may attract SEC attention. LAToken postponed opening for the US such innovation as tokenized stocks and commodities which are currently tradable on the platform in other regions. At the same time, their LAT (which is not asset linked) is open for the US as it is similar to many other utility tokens giving a credit to pay for future platform usage such as assets tokenization, KYC, transactions etc.”  https://techcrunch.com/2017/09/14/sec-shows-support-for-icos-that-are-not-obviously-securities/

Author: panteraforlife
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Liquid asset-backed tokens (LABT) are the tokens issued at the LAT platform to allow fractional ownership of assets sold at the LAT platform. LABT are issued on the Ethereum platform by means of the ERC20 smart contract. A third-party Trustee will hold the actual asset and retain the seller’s option to buy back the asset from the LABT holders at market price on the settlement date. If the seller refuses to exercise the option, the asset will be sold at fiat auction by the trustee and LABT holders are entitled to receive their corresponding share of the proceeds.

Author: panteraforlife
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: There are also special LABT tokens, there are issued for every specific iten tokenized on the platform. For example an hotel in NY would have it's tokens by the name - LABTHOTELNY1 and a resort in Brussels would have it's tokens  named - LABTRESORTBRUS1.

Author: andrewjchapin
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: The four points of the Howey Test: - Is it an investment of money? Yes. - Is there an expectation of profits from the investment? ICO buyers are buying LAT knowing that the token is backed by real assets, not purchasing for anything other than a financial gain. - Is the investment of money in a common enterprise? Yes, per the broad vertical definition of a common enterprise. "The investors are dependent upon the expertise or efforts of the investment promoter for their returns." - Are profits coming from the efforts of a promoter or third party? Bounty program, staged discounts, etc. can fit into this category - when the end-user buys at a 15% discount from the efforts of a third party (BTT signature), they're going to be able to profit easier/differently than the market. Not quite kosher.  Other red flags: - In practice, does this idea make any sense? The "how it works" section seems to indicate that I, an asset owner, could effectively take out a mortgage on my asset (trading part of it/all of it on the exchange for $) and then effectively "buy it back" later. But with the likely shift in value of the token, how do I know what it'll cost to buy it back? It's possible that I sell half of my $500k USD house for 1000 LAT (round number for the sake of simplicity), then watch the value of 1000 LAT go from $250k USD to $1m USD. That's what I have to pay, or the custodian will auction it off? Just seems like a reckless thing to do as an asset owner. What makes this better than working with a traditional bank? - The token sale distribution seems staged for serious market manipulation. 20% for the vague "network growth" doesn't give me confidence that the organization will allow the markets to behave normally. If I put up an asset, seems like it will be easy for the organization to pump or deflate the price to influence my ability to buy it back, while they are able to auction it off for fiat. - Heavy time-based incentives mean that people's cost-basis for LAT is low (and all over the map), meaning that those who actually participate in the system are subject to likely downward market activity. Short term, I would expect manipulation to the downside while the organization collects real-life, hard assets. - The Inc. press link is broken. - The HuffPost link is to the contributor network, isn't actually a real HuffPo post. (Anyone can do this.)

Author: Greenlee
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Either at the day expiration or before that a client may choose to trade out of his position by simply selling it or by waiting till the end of the expiration day and receive respective amount of LAT in return for expired contract. The expiration price will be calculated as a close price of real world asset (Apple share on respective exchange for example) for that trading day divided by the average rate of LAT/EUR over 24 hours (if we will be able to list LAT on exchange before the end of September), or by an average rate of ETH/EUR over 24 hours times the fixed price of LAT/ETH depending on ICO round). The company runs market making operations currently, thus the bids are available 24/7. A client is free to choose either to hold his tokenized shares till last day of trading or trade off his position before that.

Author: badman74
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: There is a good part in the WP. About how they tokenize art-works. Check it out - Artwork tokenization and trade Step 1. Application for sale The owner of the artwork fills in the form on the LAT platform for artwork-backed token issue, providing basic asset information, results of previous appraisals (if available), share of asset to be tokenized, and ownership rights. Step 2. Asset appraisal Prior to artwork tokenization, it is subject to tests for authenticity, appraisal, and insurance by LAT-certified vendors. Step 3. Custodial agreement The LAT-certified custodian and the applicant sign a binding agreement for mandatory future open fiat auction by the settlement date. Step 4. Asset tokenization and sale When all legal issues are settled, LABT backed by the artwork are issued on the LAT exchange and become available for investors. All raised funds are transferred to the seller. Step 5. Asset buy back By the settlement date, the applicant must sell his artwork at a fiat auction and distribute the proceeds among the LABT holders. If he fails to do this, the asset will be sold at a fiat auction by the Trustee.

Author: panteraforlife
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: About the potential - these are the markets LATtoken are already working with. EQUITY (global asset value - 65 trillion$) - Listing equity on a stock exchange is a very costly process. Underwriters and bookrunners syndicate fees are ranging from 2% to over 6%1 of gross proceeds from the offering, application and filing fees fee average around $25k. DEBT (g.a.v - 215 trillion$) - Issuing debt on a leading stock exchange incurs initial listing fees of ~$20,000 and an annual fee of ~$20,0004 . Underwriting fees generally amount over 1% of total gross proceeds from debt issuance. REAL ESTATE (g.a.v - 217 trillion$) - On average home sellers pay their listing agent a commission of about 6% of the price. Other transaction costs amount to ~5% and include escrow costs and recording costs upon sale, title insurance costs. The sale process takes on average not less than 65 days. The proceeds from the real estate sale are taxed at the rate of up to 20% . ART WORKS (g.a.v - 3 trillion$) - As per example below seller fees associated with an artwork sale are 20-25% of the sale price (hummer price) while buyer’s premium charged up to 25% (according to Sotheby’s commission structure). LAT can greatly reduce all these costs. This alone already has really huge potential.

Insurances will be used.

Author: Greenlee
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Know your customer (KYC) refers to due diligence activities that financial institutions and other regulated companies must perform to ascertain relevant information from their clients for the purpose of doing business with them. The term is also used to refer to the bank regulation which governs these activities. Know Your Customer processes are also employed by companies of all sizes for the purpose of ensuring their proposed agents', consultants' or distributors' anti-bribery compliance. Banks, insurers and export credit agencies are increasingly demanding that customers provide detailed anti-corruption due diligence information, to verify their probity and integrity.

Author: Greenlee
Title: [ANN] 🔵 LATOKEN - Multi-Asset Trading Platform 🔵
Body: Standing for "Anti-money Laundering", it is a set of procedures, laws or regulations designed to stop the practice of generating income through illegal actions. In most cases money launderers hide their actions through a series of steps that make it look like money coming from illegal or unethical sources was earned legitimately.
